<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Annual accountability hearing with the Care Quality Commission - Health Committee - June 2011 (report published 14 September 2</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence by the Department of Health</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (PHE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">0021</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Annual accountability hearing with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Public Health England November </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">201</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This memorandum has been prepared for the Health Committee by the Department of Health</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (DH)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to assist</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in its </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">first </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">annual review meeting with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Public Health England (PHE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">). The DH </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is grateful for the opportunity to contribute to this proce</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ss</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and outline PHE’s achievements</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> over i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ts first six months.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Government created PHE </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as an executive agency of DH </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the national expert body providing public health expertise across the range of public health, including health protection, health improvement and healthcare public health (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">i.e.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the population health aspects of clinical services). PHE delivers Secretary of State’s duty to protect the health of the population, and also carries out his statutory role in joint appointments of Directors of Public Health to local authorities. It supports local authorities in taking forward their duty to improve the health of their populations, not least through providing the evidence base and advice on best practice. Last but not least, PHE provides expertise on the population aspects of clinical commissioning and is the public health adviser to NHS England. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A set of key objectives were developed for the transition</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to the new arrangements</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. These were that PHE must be:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">fully operational</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, with all functions transferred safely, to ensure no “dip” in delivery;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">credible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> - capable of managing relationships with other parts of the system effectively;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Positioned</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to achieve improvements in service and outcomes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">with its </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">leadership in place, setting a clear direction with clearly identified projects to develop capability and improve performance.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These objectives have been met and overall there has been a smooth transition to the new public health system. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">On 1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> April 2013, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">took on their new full range of responsibilities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and the transfer of public health responsibilit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ies to local government</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> proceeded as planned, with no significant service delivery issues raised from the frontline.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> developed good working relationships with local authorities and NHS England as wel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">l as making progress with other</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">partners, such as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">N</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ational </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nstitute for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">linical </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">xcellence (NICE)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The strength of the new t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ripartite</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> relationship between DH, PHE and NHS England was</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> tested </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">very </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">early on by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">need to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">collaborative</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">work on planning the response to the measles outbreak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This work was a success and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has provided valuable learning on future work together.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ecruitment at national, regional and local levels</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> has taken place to support an effective and sustainable public health system</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. In particular, r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gional implementation teams have been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">established, and recruitment to the immunisation and screening posts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, which was an area of potential risk,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">being actively managed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> total of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">90</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">% of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">these </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">posts have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">now </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">been filled.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As noted above, PHE is responsible for carrying out Secretary of State’s statutory function in relation to joint appointments of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Directors of Public Health </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to local authorities. Where substantive appointments have yet to be made interim arrangements are in place, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">will continue to work with local authorities to ensure appropriate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">substantive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">appointments can be made</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">DH and PHE are working together to design and deliver leadership development programmes for aspirant Directors of Public Health to ensure a future supply of highly skilled professionals equipped for working in local government. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE have published their priorities for 2013/14 and are working on the detailed programmes to underpin delivery</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Governance arrangements </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have been established</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and work has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> started on PHE’s three-year Corporate Plan. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A key challenge is to continue to develop and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">embed strong </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">relation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ship</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s with local authorities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, NHS England </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">delivery partners </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">improve the nation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s health</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ensure </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">robust arrangements are in place locally to respond to new threats</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reate the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">conditions to enable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">staff to work across traditional boundaries to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">deliver </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">priorities and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to make </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">efficiency savings</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Background</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">The New Public Health System</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Government’s ambition is to transform the public’s health through strengthening local action, supporting self-esteem and behavioural changes, promoting healthy choices and changing the environment to support healthier lives.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The changes to the public health system </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are designed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to achieve this.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Improvement in the public’s health has to be led from within communities, rather than directed centrally.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The new system is therefore led locally by locally elected members of the 152 upper-tier authority areas in England.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">From April 2013 local authorities have had a duty to take appropriate steps to improve the health of their populations, supported by a ring-fenced public health grant.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">They also have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">duties</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to advise clinical commissioning groups on the population aspects of clinical commissioning, and to advise local partners on health protection arrangements.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As democratically-accountable bodies responsible for shaping their local communities, local authorities are ideally placed to embed public thinking into everything they do and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to influence the wider determinants of their population’s health and wellbeing, such as housing, transport, employment, pollution and poverty.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uppor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> local authorities and the wider public health</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> system</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. It </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">brings together for the first time the full range of public health expertise to protect health and address inequalities, and promote the health and wellbeing of the nation. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE works very closely with upper tier local authorities through its 15 local centres.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE provides local government with evidence and advice on what works. It allocates the ring-fenced budget to local authorities.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It also publishes data on performance against the Public Health Outcomes Framework</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">NHS </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">continue</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to play a full role in public health, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not least through using routine clinical contacts to promote healthier living.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">NHS England also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">commission</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> certain public services, such as national immunisation and screening programmes,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> through an agreement with the Department.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE provides the public health advice underpinning this agreement.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The total value of these programmes is £2.2bn in 2013/14</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">H</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> remains responsible for setting national strategies, securing resources and acc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ounting for performance.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> We have published a Public Health Out</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">comes Framework which sets out the Government’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> vision for improving health and reducing health inequalities.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE is the Department</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s expert adviser on public health matters.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">HE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">’s purpose</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE’s 