t-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he SDS supports the Permanent Secretary in holding PHE to account and providing assurance on its performance. A critical mechanism is the quarterly accountability meetings, chai</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed by the SDS and attended by the Chief Executive of PHE and other DH and PHE Directors;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he SDS is supported by a DH Sponsor Team, who is the principal day-to-day </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">liaison between the DH and PHE;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE must obtain and publish, at least annually, updated information for each local authority against the Public Health Outcomes Framework in order to give DH a clear account of progress;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE shall publish and lay before Parliament an annual report </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">describ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">es </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">performance against objectives and its use of public funds</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> including assurance that local authorities are discharging their financial obligations to improve health and wellbeing in their communities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The report shall reflect the views of external agencies and stakeholders who have dealings with PHE, including local government and the NHS.</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Chief Executive of PHE is responsible for the leadership of PHE and the delivery of its objectives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and has established appropriate governance arrangements t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> support him in achieving this.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">He</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is supported by an Advisory Board</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is responsible for providing strategic advice on the running of PHE, including assuring the effectiveness of PHE’s cor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">porate governance arrangements</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is also an Audit and Risk Committee, chaired by a Non-Executive Member, to help assure the financial and operational performance of PHE.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Operational Autonomy</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">For PHE to fulfil the Secretary of State’s statutory </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">duties</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, it is important that PHE is and is seen as a trusted and impartial champion for the protection of the health of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and free to provide advice based firmly on the science and the evidence.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The Government’s position on PHE’s operational independence was set out by Earl Howe during the course of the Third Reading debate of the Health and Social Care Bill </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on 19</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">March 2012: </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">My noble friend is anxious for Public Health England to be and to be seen to be a trusted and impartial champion for the protection of the health of the people and free to provide advice based firmly on the science and the evidence. So are we.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“It will be essential for it and the Government to work together seamlessly and to share the same objectives. Anything less could severely limit the Secretary of State's capacity to undertake his statutory duty.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“Public Health England will of course be its own master as regards the research that it undertakes, and it will be operationally independent, as I emphasised earlier.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“My noble friend Lady Cumberlege asked me whether PHE will be able to give professional advice freely to the public. We expect it to do precisely that, in much the same way that the Chief Medical Officer already does. It will be good practice for PHE and the department to consult each other about communications on public health matters, but with a view to agreeing the content, not censoring it. PHE data will be subject to the code of practice on official statistics, which severely restricts access to certain material by Ministers or officials before it is published. Within three years of PHE becoming operational we will undertake a review of its governance to ensure that it is entirely appropriate and effective</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Pr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ogress</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">noted above, there has been a generally smooth transition to the new arrangements. For example, in response to the national increase in measles cases and the recent outbreak in Wales, the national PHE team worked with NHS England and DH to launch a national catch-up programme to vaccinate 10-16 year old children. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is now responsible for commissioning Change4Life and other health promotion campaigns</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Change4Life is Public Health England’s flagship obesity prevention campaign and a key aspect of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">their work programme. Change4Life encourages everyone in England to ‘eat well, move more, live longer’ with a specific focus on lower-income families with 5-11 year old children. The campaign has enjoyed considerable success and unparalleled levels of engagement since its launch in 2009.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE’s national 28 Day Stop Smoking Challenge - Stoptober - ran again</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in Autumn 2013. There were 1.25</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">million visits to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> website during the campaign period, and nearly 500,000 Stoptober support products were ordered included packs, apps, text and email support.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> April</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> published five high-level </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">priorities for 2013/2014:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Helping people to live longer and more healthy lives by reducing preventable deaths and the burden of ill health associated with smoking, high blood pressure, obesity, poor diet, poor mental health, insufficient exercise, and alcohol</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Reducing the burden of disease and disability in life by focusing on preventing and recovering from the conditions with the greatest impact, including dementia, anxiety, depression and drug dependency</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Protecting the country from infectious diseases and environmental hazards, including the growing problem of infections that resist treatment with antibiotics</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Supporting families to give children and young people the best start in life, through working with health visiting and school nursing, family nurse partnerships and the Troubled Families programme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Improving health in the workplace by encouraging employers to support their staff, and those moving into and out of the workforce, to lead healthier lives.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Future Challenges</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Government believes that PHE has made a good start and looks forward to the Agency building on this foundation to maximise its impact on the public’s health. In particular, PHE is well-placed to support local authorities in making improving the public’s health core to everything they do; and to support national priorities such as combatting antimicrobial resistance. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> PHE boasts many scientists and programmes of international standing. It will be important that PHE maintains and develops this inheritance in the years to come. A crucial part of this will be ensuring appropriate reprovisioning of Category 4 laboratory services, potentially as part of a PHE Science Hub bringing together key parts of PHE’s national infrastructure. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Given the continuing downward pressure on public spending it will be vital that PHE maximises operational efficiencies through strategies such as shared business services and develops a commercial strategy to increase its income. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span></p><ol start="36" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In the six months since its formal go-live date,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">successfully welcomed over</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 5000 staff </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and created a well-functioning organisation. PHE’s performance in areas such as the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">MMR catch-up campaign</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> demonstrates encouraging</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> progress</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="37" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Inevitably there has been a focus on setting up new systems and relationships and building a new organisation – a process which will take time.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">DH and PHE are working closely together to ensure that there is a robust but constructive accountability relationship between the centre and PHE.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As part of DH but operationally autonomous, PHE has the oppo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rtunity to influence but still “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">speak truth to power”.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="38" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ccountability for delivery in the new public health system is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> rightly at local level and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PHE is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uniquely positioned to provide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">leadership, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advice </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and support as necessary</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Department of Health</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">October </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">201</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/framework-agreement-between-the-department-of-health-and-public-health-england"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/framework-agreement-between-the-department-of-health-and-public-health-england</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:9pt">The Chair and non-executive members are appointed by the Secretary of State for Health.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:9pt">DH and PHE are currently in the process of recruiting two more non-executive members.</span></p></body></html>